### Central Thesis

Benny Blanco is an Enneagram Type 2 whose entire career, home life, and marriage run on one pattern: manufacturing comfort for others as a survival strategy against a fear of being unlovable that predates the music.

### Thread Map

Cold open (comfort engineering, "what is all that comfort for?") → diagnosis (Type 2, Stern role-play as tiebreaker) → the method in the studio → childhood origin (the "mmph" ritual: caretaking before music) → success and breakdown at 21 (the recovery toolbox gets catered out too) → the same machine at home (house menu) → the marriage and the mockery (can he believe he'd be chosen for himself?) → the fame paradox (holds rooms, hates standing in front of them) → close (breakfast as the adult "mmph"). Every section serves the thesis; the ending lands the exact question the intro opened.

